Package utilities

Class PropertyManager

java.lang.Object
utilities.PropertyManager
public class PropertyManager extends Object
PropertyManager is a utility class that is used to read data from a configuration file and make it available for use in other parts of the application. It uses the singleton design pattern to ensure that only one instance of the class is created and used throughout the application.

  • Method Details

    • getInstance

      public static PropertyManager getInstance()
      This method returns an instance of the PropertyManager class, creating a new instance if one does not already exist. It also calls the loadData() method to load data from the configuration file.
      Returns:
      instance of PropertyManager

    • loadData

      private void loadData()
      This method reads data from the 'configuration.properties' file using the Properties class. It sets the values of the different properties (url, validUsername, etc.) according to the values in the configuration file. If an IOException occurs while reading the file, the exception is printed to the console.
